-- Daewoo, AXPO Bid to Build TE Plant in Croatia, Energetika Says
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2012-09-17T13:08:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-17/daewoo-axpo-bid-to-build-te-plant-in-croatia-energetika-says.html
Daewoo Engineering and Construction
Co. Ltd.  in a joint bid with Australia’s  Macquarie Group Ltd. (MQG) ,
as well as Switzerland’s Axpo Holding AG and Italy’s Edison SpA
are among six bidders for building a thermoelectric plant in
Croatia, portal  Energetika  said today, citing unidentified
people at the national grid Hrvatska Elektroprivreda d.d.  The plant will have a capacity of 500 megawatts and cost
800 million euros ($1 billion) to build, Alenka Ducic, a
spokeswoman at the  Economy Ministry , said by phone today. HEP
said last week it will select bidders by Sept. 28.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
